# Root-level generated files (ENFORCEMENT - MUST BE IN tmp/ OR docs/archive/)
# *** CRITICAL RULE: All generated data goes to ./tmp/ ***
# Do NOT create or commit: .md reports, .txt reports, .json output, logs, screenshots, etc. in root
#
# ALLOWED in root ONLY: package.json, package-lock.json, README.md, .gitignore, .dockerignore, Makefile
#
# Generated files placement:
#   - Test results → tmp/test-results/
#   - Reports → tmp/reports/
#   - Screenshots → tmp/screenshots/
#   - Logs → tmp/logs/
#   - Build artifacts → tmp/build/
#   - Temporary data → tmp/data/
#   - Historical records → docs/archive/generated/ (if tracked in git)
#   - Handoff docs → docs/handoffs/ (for future developers)
#
# Examples (WRONG → RIGHT):
#   ./PHASE1-COMPLETION.md → ./docs/archive/generated/PHASE1-COMPLETION.md
#   ./test-results.json → ./tmp/test-results/test-results.json
#   ./debug.log → ./tmp/logs/debug.log
#   ./screenshot-0.png → ./tmp/screenshots/screenshot-0.png
#
# Reference: docs/DATA-ORGANIZATION-ENFORCEMENT.md

# Keep examples/ tracked (but not generated artifacts inside them)
# Structure:
#   examples/api-usage/ - track source examples
#   examples/forensic-export/ - track source examples
#   examples/integration/ - track source examples

# Runtime outputs and state files
*.state
*.cache
*.session
runtime-cache/

# Generated API documentation (auto-built from registry at startup)
openapi.json
openapi.yaml
api-schema.json

# ── Large test-artifact & screenshot dumps (cleaned 2026-07) ──
# Regenerable junk; old copies remain recoverable via `git checkout origin/main -- <path>`.
/archives/
/screenshots/
/results/
/reports/
/coverage/
**/test-screenshots/
**/test-artifacts-*/
# Python caches (rag-app, mcp, clients)
.pytest_cache/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
# Dev TLS certs — generate locally, never commit private keys
/certs/
*.pem
*.key
